</front><body><![CDATA[   <B>     <P align="center"><font size="4"><a name="titulo"></a>RESUMOS/<I>ABSTRACTS</I><a href="#nota">*</a></font></P>     <P align="left">&nbsp;</P>     <P align="left">&nbsp;</P>     <P align="left"><font size="3">PENSAR O BRASIL</font></P> </B>     <P align="left"><B></b><font size="3">Por ocasi&atilde;o dos 25 anos de exist&ecirc;ncia    do Centro de Estudos de Cultura Contempor&acirc;nea - CEDEC um grupo de intelectuais    convidados discute tr&ecirc;s dimens&otilde;es do problema de pensar o Brasil.    S&atilde;o elas: por que pensar, como se pensa e como pensar. As exposi&ccedil;&otilde;es    e debates cobrem a totalidade deste n&uacute;mero da revista.</font></P>     <P align="left">&nbsp;</P> <B>     <P ALIGN="left"><font size="3">BRAZILIAN THROUGHT ON BRAZIL</font></P> </B><I>    <P ALIGN="left"><font size="3">On the 25th anniversary of  the Center for Contemporary Cultural Studies – CEDEC, a group of invited  intellectuals discuss three dimensions of the problem of how Brazilian throught faces Brazil as its object. They are: why to think, how it has been thought, and how to think.</font>  </P>     <P ALIGN="left">&nbsp;  </P>     ]]></body>
